function.arguments: {"instructions": "Which of these animals are found in Africa?"}

chat_history.content:
Based on my search, the top five heaviest animals in the world are:

1. Blue Whale - The blue whale is known as the heaviest animal on Earth, with the largest blue whale recorded weighing approximately 190 metric tons.
2. Fin Whale - Coming in second is the fin whale, with an average weight of around 72 metric tons.
3. North Pacific Right Whale - The North Pacific right whale is the third heaviest, often weighing between 60 and 80 metric tons.
4. Southern Elephant Seal - This massive mammal can weigh up to 5,000 kg and is the largest of all seals.
5. African Elephant - The largest land mammal in the world, the African elephant, can weigh up to 6,350 kg.
